      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is this something we can/should be doing for all these OSS-Fuzzers?  Like, create a new source file that contains something like this, and link it with each of these little files that\u0027d define skia_fuzz_entrypoint()?\n\n    #include \"Fuzz.h\"\n\n    // / Don\u0027t print the list of LSAN suppressions on every execution.\n    __attribute__((no_sanitize(\"address\", \"memory\", \"thread\", \"undefined\")))\n    __attribute__((visibility(\"default\")))\n    __attribute__((used))\n    extern \"C\" const char *__lsan_default_options() {\n        return \"print_suppressions\u003d0\";\n    }\n\n    void skia_fuzz_entrypoint(Fuzz*);\n\n    extern \"C\" int LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput(const uint8_t *data, size_t size) {\n        auto fuzz \u003d Fuzz(SkData::MakeWithoutCopy(data, size));\n        skia_fuzz_entrypoint(\u0026fuzz);\n        return 0;\n    }\n\nOr can we just not do this in code at all, and set it in the environment when running?",
